# Use the full public display viewport

TV and wall **display** builds (`apps/display/**`) run edge-to-edge on a fixed screen. Every screen and layout must use **100% of available width and height** — no unused letterboxing, floating islands, or clipped content from vertical centering.

## Root shell

- Fill the viewport: `fixed inset-0 overflow-hidden` or `h-dvh w-full overflow-hidden`.
- Prefer **`dvh`** over `vh` when using viewport height units.
- Avoid page-level `max-w-*` wrappers (`max-w-7xl`, `max-w-screen-xl`, etc.) that cap content width on full-screen routes.

## Height chain (flex / grid)

- Column layouts: outer `flex flex-col h-full min-h-0`; scrollable/main regions `flex-1 min-h-0`.
- Every flex/grid ancestor between root and a growing child needs **`min-h-0`** (or `min-w-0` for horizontal shrink).
- Do **not** use `justify-center` + fixed/min heights on the main stage if it can push content under the header or clip the bottom — distribute space with `flex-1` instead.

## Width chain

- Prefer `w-full max-w-none` on top-level layout rows; let columns share space with `flex-1 min-w-0` or explicit tracks.
- Fixed-width side panels are fine when the **row still spans full width** and the center column gets `flex-1`.
- Avoid large horizontal margins/padding that leave permanent empty gutters unless they are intentional inner padding inside a full-bleed shell.

## Content sizing

- Scale typography and spacing with **`clamp()`**, **`vmin`/`vmax`**, or container queries — not fixed px blocks that leave dead space on large TVs.
- Prefer **`overflow-hidden` + internal layout** over `overflow-y-auto` on the main stage (scroll is a last resort on venue displays).
- Do not use `h-[calc(100vh-200px)]`-style magic offsets when a flex column with header + `flex-1` main achieves the same fit.

## Checklist before merging display layout changes

- [ ] Root view fills width and height with no obvious unused bands on left/right or top/bottom.
- [ ] Main content area grows with `flex-1 min-h-0` (or equivalent grid `minmax(0, 1fr)`).
- [ ] No accidental `max-w-*` or `mx-auto` centering that shrinks the layout on a full-screen route.
- [ ] Test at wide (16:9 TV) and short heights — nothing overlaps the header or clips below the fold.

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Full viewport shell + growing main
<div className="fixed inset-0 flex min-h-0 flex-col overflow-hidden">
  <header className="shrink-0">…</header>
  <main className="flex min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-hidden">…</main>
</div>

// ❌ Capped width on a wall screen
<div className="mx-auto max-w-7xl flex-1">…</div>

// ❌ Vertical centering that steals height from the stage
<main className="flex flex-1 items-center justify-center min-h-[720px]">…</main>
```
